		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://ocharowca.info/geceao/?p=52</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[In collaboration with ECOWAS, IFRC and OCHA the ninth Annual Consultation of the Regional Committee for Disaster Management in West Africa (GECEAO) is scheduled to take place in Abidjan, Côte d’Ivoire, from 8-10 June 2015. The regional consultation will bring together representatives of the Disaster Management Agencies/Civil Protection Directorates of &#8230;]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In collaboration with ECOWAS, IFRC and OCHA the ninth <em>Annual Consultation of the Regional Committee for Disaster Management in West Africa</em> (GECEAO) is scheduled to take place in Abidjan, Côte d’Ivoire, from <strong>8-10 June 2015</strong>.</p>
<p>The regional consultation will bring together representatives of the Disaster Management Agencies/Civil Protection Directorates of the ECOWAS countries plus Mauritania, country and regional representatives for the IFRC and the UN as well as thematic experts.</p>
<p>This year’s consultation will focus on the following key topics :</p>
<ul>
<li>Regional Multi Risk Analysis and Preparedness Measures;</li>
<li>Regional and sub-regional initiatives on Preparedness and Emergency Response;</li>
<li>The Ebola Virus Disease Crisis in West Africa: best practices and lessons learnt;</li>
<li>Lessons learnt from the Fogo Volcanic eruption;</li>
<li>Migration and protection challenges;</li>
<li>GECEAO Priorities and Work plan.</li>
</ul>
<p>This event will provide a unique opportunity to share experiences, draw lessons and identify best practices and enhance south to south cooperation.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
